  "special": {
    "title": "Gun, Gunner!",
    "description": "Consumes 2 ammo per shot and fires a piercing, rocket-like projectile. When it hits inert surfaces such as walls or the ground, it creates a series of delayed follow-up blasts. The projectiles count as rockets for absorption effects, allowing pistol ammo to be converted into launcher ammo with an absorb shield."
  },
  "notes": "When fired into the ground with an absorb shield, it can convert pistol rounds into launcher ammo, often generating several rockets per shot. The Sham is especially popular for this because its high absorb chance lowers the risk of self-damage. It is always incendiary, so it performs poorly against shields. Redundant variants spend more ammo but create more blasts. Amp shields boost the explosions fully, and if a direct piercing hit fails to register, aiming at enemies' feet usually lets the blast pattern do the work.",
